Description: Fragment of flattened handle from neck join to sharpish turn of a Rhodian pottery transport amphora. Clay fine buff. Rectangular stamp with grape cluster symbol.
Curator's comments: Ink, deleted, '54'. Name Themison. From same die as Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, ABC 0630.15.
Bibliographic references: Stoddart 1847 / Memoir on the inscribed pottery of Rhodes, Cnidus and other Greek Cities (249)
